{
 "name": "RPlog_Disturber_of_Inner_Peace",
 "title": "Disturber of Inner Peace",
 "summary": "In the tranquil solarium of the Jedi temple on New Alderaan, Ambassador Ambrosia and her restless young daughter Gabi watch the sunset until the ostentatious Imperial-mannered Zeak Oppenhiemer strolls in and disrupts their peace. Oppenhiemer reveals he has come to collect Ara, her brother, and their tutor for an extended family vacation aboard his retrofitted cruiser, and he presses Ambrosia to let Gabi, and even her whole staff, come along. Gabi, owed a proper birthday after a harrowing previous year, eagerly campaigns for the trip, while Ambrosia deflects, citing her imminent posting to Kashyyyk and the need to gather information firsthand about villages vanishing under apparent superstition. Oppenhiemer offers a thinly veiled paramilitary 'investment', a frigate, fighters, and mercenaries with plausible deniability, to speed the Kashyyyk situation along, which Ambrosia politely declines for now, insisting they first need better intelligence. She promises Gabi they will spend her birthday together and noncommittally agrees to consider the vacation offer before ushering her daughter off to bed and bidding Oppenhiemer good night.",
